<title> Sreerama K. Murthy  </title>
<h1> Sreerama K. Murthy </h1>

<body>
If you accessed this page via <strong> http://www.cs.jhu.edu/grad/murthy, 
</strong> please note that the correct link is <strong> 
http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy. </strong> The old address may not work in 
the future. 
<br> <br>
I moved from Johns Hopkins University to the Imaging & Visualization 
department at <!WA0><a href =
"http://www.siemens.com/"> Siemens </a> Corporate Research, Princeton,
New Jersey in November 95. <!WA1><a href = "http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy/address.html">Contact information</a>. 
<br> <br>
A PostScript version of my (outdated) resume is <!WA2><a href = "http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy/resume.ps">here</a>.

<br> <br>
<hr>
<h3> Research </h3>
I am interested in solving real-world <strong>
classification </strong> and <strong> prediction </strong> problems
using <strong> machine learning </strong> and other data analysis 
techniques. My current domain of interest is <strong>
medical image analysis </strong>. I am very interested in <strong> knowledge
discovery </strong> from data repositories. <br> <br>

<br>
<hr>
<h3> <!WA3><a href="http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy/thesis/home.html"> Ph.D. Thesis </a> </h3>

I spent a lot of time putting up my Ph.D. thesis online. As a guest at this
site, it is your moral obligation to check it out! There is a 
<!WA4><a href = "http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy/thesis/latex2html/thesis.html"> HTML version </a> that allows 
selective retrieval of just about any portion you want. You may
also retrieve the <!WA5><a href="http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~murthy/thesis/home.html"> compressed PostScript files 
</a> for individual chapters or the whole thesis. 
<br> <br>
<!WA6><a href="mailto:murthy@scr.siemens.com"> Comments? </a>
<BR> <BR>
<hr>
<h3> Alma Maters </h3>

Before coming to <!WA7><a href="http://www.cs.jhu.edu"> Department of 
Computer Science </a> at <!WA8><a href="http://www.jhu.edu"> Johns Hopkins 
University </a>, I was at Department of Computer Science and Engineering, 
<!WA9><a href="http://sol.rutgers.edu/~sabesan/iitm.html"> Indian Institute of
Technology </a> (1988-1990) and at Department of Computer Science, 
<!WA10><a href="http://www.cs.umsl.edu/~sanjiv/mnrec.html"> M. N. Regional Engineering
College </a> (1984-1988).
<br> <br>
